title: South Africa Three Month Interbank Rate
description: South Africa Three Month Interbank Rate was at 6.56 percent on Wednesday November 9. Interbank Rate in South Africa averaged 7.73 percent from 1999 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 16.96 percent in February of 1999 and a record low of 3.33 percent in October of 2020. In South Africa, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides - South Africa Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: South African Reserve Bank
